title: bookcaseExamine
---
[nomarkup][The books are placed together in disorganized chaos - with no rhyme or reason to their presence.][/nomarkup]
<<if Roll ("Intelligence","Awareness")>=4>>
    [nomarkup][That is, they are at first glance... When you examine them more closely, you notice a pattern. Several titles that can be directly linked to something known as the “Hidden Arts” repeat themselves, and a volume of one of them seems to be especially heavily used... It is titled: “The Book of Law” by Aleister Crowley.][/nomarkup]
    <<set $hiddenArts to true>>
    <<if Roll ("Intelligence","Occult") >=5>>
        [nomarkup][Aleister Crowley... You recognize that name. He was a prominent English occultist and ceremonial magician. If he's in a vampire's bookshelf, then maybe not all of his body of work is nonsense...][/nomarkup]
    <<elseif Roll ("Wits","Occult")>=3>> 
        [nomarkup][The “Hidden Arts”, huh? Sounds paranormal enough. You probably shouldn't touch the volume...][/nomarkup]
    <<endif>>
<<if $hiddenArts == true>>
    -> {$pcName}: [nomarkup][Take the book.][/nomarkup]
<<endif>>
    {$kieran}: [nomarkup][He stops you before you can touch the cover.][/nomarkup] Let me check them first. I do not think there is a trap, but with matters of the occult, you're better safe than sorry.
-> {$pcName}: Diana has quite the collection. She appears to read this one quite often, though. [nomarkup][You point at it.][/nomarkup]
    {$kieran}: [nomarkup][He looks for a while at the book you pointed out and its volumes.][/nomarkup] Liber Al vel Legis by Aleister Crowley. Good eyes. Let me check them first. I do not think there is a trap, but with matters of the occult, you're better safe than sorry. (+1 Kieran influence)
    <<ModifyInfluence 1 $kieran>>
<<jump booksHaveTeeth>>
===
title: booksHaveTeeth
---
<<if GetIsPartyMemberRecruited($anastasia) is true>>
    {$anastasia}: What? Now even books have teeth?
    {$kieran}: If they have some, you just have to gently stroke their spine. You weren't aware, Ms. Goth Queen? [nomarkup][He chuckles.][/nomarkup]
<<endif>>
{$kieran}: [nomarkup][He examines the book for a while without taking it from the shelf.][/nomarkup] Everything looks to be in order.
[nomarkup][You remove the book from its shelf and open it up to a random page - leafing through it. There's nothing special about it, at first glance. No marks, no hidden compartments cut into the pages...][/nomarkup]
<<if Roll ("Wits","Insight")>=4>>
    -> {$pcName}: Diana doesn't seem like the religious type, to me...
    <<set $thelema to true>>
    <<if GetIsPartyMemberRecruited($anastasia) is true>>
        {$anastasia}: She, at the very least, does seem to believe in anarchy. For those people, it's hard to say that organized religion doesn't represent an unjustified hierarchy.
        -> {$pcName}: I'm not talking about that. This book is like a Bible, for Thelema; she consults it often.
    <<endif>>
    {$kieran}: Well, it is often the first stop for any wannabe magician. Maybe she's finally decided to start doing her homework?
<<endif>>
<<if Roll ("Intelligence","Academics")>=4>>
    -> {$pcName}: It looks like Diana is interested in some majorly esoteric stuff. Does Kate know?
    <<set $thelema to true>>
    {$kieran}: [nomarkup][He thinks for a second and shakes his head.][/nomarkup] I don't think so. Like I said, she never showed interest in this stuff. [nomarkup][He rubs his forehead.][nomarkup] I don't know what may have happened to change that. Maybe her reason for reading it so diligently is more about Thelema, not magick in particular?
<<endif>>
<<if Roll ("Resolve","Investigation")>=4>>
    -> {$pcName}: [nomarkup][You thoroughly examine the book's cover, revealing a small monogram on the front page.][/nomarkup] Do you recognize that symbol, Kieran?
    <<set $thelema to true>>
    {$kieran}: [nomarkup][He stares at it intensely for a few moments.][/nomarkup] It's not one that I know of, nor is it Thelema's hexagram. Maybe it's someone's sigil? I am sure it's not Kate's, at the very least.
-> [nomarkup][On second thought, I don't want to look at this dusty, old book.][/nomarkup]
<<if $thelema == true>>
    [nomarkup][You don't think you'll find anything else in this book... You put it back on the shelf.][/nomarkup]
<<jump bookcase>>
